/*
====================================================================
üìò Lecture Notes:
Pattern Printing ‚Äì PART 3 (HARD LEVEL)
180 Days Coding Challenge
(Teacher‚Äôs Full Classroom Teaching Style ‚Äì COMPLETE RECONSTRUCTION)
====================================================================

‚ö†Ô∏è These notes are NOT summarized.
‚ö†Ô∏è Hinglish language is intentional.
‚ö†Ô∏è Sir‚Äôs thinking, pauses, and reasoning are preserved.
‚ö†Ô∏è This is a SINGLE GitHub-ready file.
‚ö†Ô∏è Written exactly the way a teacher explains on board.

====================================================================
*/

#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

int main()
{
    /*
    ============================================================
    1Ô∏è‚É£ CLASS OPENING ‚Äì REALITY & CONNECTION
    ============================================================

    "Hello, kaise ho aap sab log?"

    "Main jaanta hoon aap sab achhe se coding kar rahe ho."

    Sir shares real incident:

    "Yaar aaj thodi si dikkat ho gayi.
     Hum 2 ghante ki recording kar rahe the,
     lekin audio chala gaya."

    "Isliye aaj backup ke liye mobile phone use kar rahe hain."

    Important teacher mindset:
    ‚ùù Padhai rukni nahi chahiye ‚ùû

    ============================================================
    */


    /*
    ============================================================
    2Ô∏è‚É£ LECTURE CONTEXT ‚Äì PATTERN PRINTING PART 3
    ============================================================

    Sir announces clearly:

    "Aaj hum Pattern Printing ka PART 3 padhne wale hain."

    Breakdown:
    ‚Ä¢ Part 1 ‚Üí Basic patterns
    ‚Ä¢ Part 2 ‚Üí Medium patterns
    ‚Ä¢ Part 3 ‚Üí HARD LEVEL patterns üî•

    "Abhi tak hum seedhe patterns print kar rahe the.
     Aaj thoda dimag lagana padega."

    ============================================================
    */


    /*
    ============================================================
    3Ô∏è‚É£ FIRST HARD QUESTION ‚Äì GIVEN PATTERN
    ============================================================

    Sir draws on board:

                *
              * *
            * * *
          * * * *
        * * * * *

    Sir asks:
    "Is pattern ko kaise print karoge?"

    Warning:
    "Yeh DIRECT pattern nahi hai.
     Sirf star print karne se kaam nahi chalega."

    ============================================================
    */


    /*
    ============================================================
    4Ô∏è‚É£ MOST IMPORTANT THINKING STEP ‚Äì OBSERVATION
    ============================================================

    Sir slows down the class:

    "Pehle dekho, print karne se pehle socho."

    Observation:
    ‚Ä¢ Har row me pehle SPACE aa raha hai
    ‚Ä¢ Uske baad STAR aa raha hai

    Conclusion:
    üëâ Pattern = SPACE + STAR

    "Agar space ka logic samajh aa gaya,
     to pattern printing easy ho jaayegi."

    ============================================================
    */


    /*
    ============================================================
    5Ô∏è‚É£ ROW-WISE ANALYSIS (VERY IMPORTANT)
    ============================================================

    Total rows = 5

    Row 1:
        Spaces = 4
        Stars  = 1

    Row 2:
        Spaces = 3
        Stars  = 2

    Row 3:
        Spaces = 2
        Stars  = 3

    Row 4:
        Spaces = 1
        Stars  = 4

    Row 5:
        Spaces = 0
        Stars  = 5

    Sir asks:
    "Stars ka formula kya hai?"

    Answer:
    ‚≠ê Stars = row number

    Sir asks:
    "Spaces ka formula kya hai?"

    Answer:
    ‚≠ê Spaces = totalRows - row

    Here:
    totalRows = 5

    So:
    üëâ Spaces = 5 - row

    ============================================================
    */


    /*
    ============================================================
    6Ô∏è‚É£ FINAL LOGIC (BOARD PE LIKHA HUA)
    ============================================================

    Step 1:
    Loop row from 1 to 5

    Step 2 (inside row loop):
    ‚Ä¢ Print (5 - row) spaces
    ‚Ä¢ Print (row) stars
    ‚Ä¢ Go to next line

    Sir says:
    "Jo hum dimag me soch rahe hain,
     wahi ab code banega."

    ============================================================
    */


    cout << "Right Aligned Star Pattern (Hard Level)\n\n";

    for(int row = 1; row <= 5; row++)
    {
        /*
        --------------------------------------------------------
        STEP 1: PRINT SPACES
        --------------------------------------------------------

        space = 1 se (5 - row) tak
        */

        for(int space = 1; space <= (5 - row); space++)
        {
            cout << "  ";   // double space for alignment
        }

        /*
        --------------------------------------------------------
        STEP 2: PRINT STARS
        --------------------------------------------------------

        star = 1 se row tak
        */

        for(int star = 1; star <= row; star++)
        {
            cout << "* ";
        }

        // STEP 3: Move to next row
        cout << endl;
    }


    /*
    ============================================================
    7Ô∏è‚É£ DRY RUN ‚Äì COMPUTER KAISE SOCHTA HAI
    ============================================================

    row = 1
    spaces = 5 - 1 = 4
    stars  = 1

    row = 2
    spaces = 3
    stars  = 2

    row = 3
    spaces = 2
    stars  = 3

    row = 4
    spaces = 1
    stars  = 4

    row = 5
    spaces = 0
    stars  = 5

    row = 6
    condition false ‚Üí loop ends

    Sir explains:
    "Computer ko pattern nahi dikhta,
     usko sirf numbers aur loops dikhte hain."

    ============================================================
    */


    /*
    ============================================================
    8Ô∏è‚É£ COMMON STUDENT MISTAKES (SIR WARNING)
    ============================================================

    ‚ùå Direct star print karna
    ‚ùå Space logic ignore karna
    ‚ùå Pattern ko yaad karna, samajhna nahi

    ‚úî Always break pattern into:
      SPACE PART
      STAR PART

    ============================================================
    */


    /*
    ============================================================
    9Ô∏è‚É£ SIR‚ÄôS FINAL ADVICE
    ============================================================

    "Aaj ka lecture samajh aaya ho
     to khud se ek aur pattern try karo."

    "Next class me:
     ‚Ä¢ Pyramid
     ‚Ä¢ Inverted pyramid
     ‚Ä¢ Diamond pattern"

    "Practice bina soche mat karna.
     Sochoge to coder banoge."

    ============================================================
    */

    return 0;
}

/*
====================================================================
END OF LECTURE ‚Äì PATTERN PRINTING PART 3 (HARD LEVEL)
====================================================================
*/
